## ESPN API and Historical Player Discovery

The ESPN roster endpoint (`/teams/{id}/roster?season=YYYY`) only returns players for the **current season**. Historical seasons return 0 players. To load historical data, `load-season.ts` uses a multi-pass approach:

1. **Current roster pass**: Fetch current (2025) rosters to discover active players and their ESPN IDs.
2. **Gamelog pass**: Fetch each player's gamelog for the target season, collecting event IDs.
3. **Boxscore discovery pass**: For each event ID, fetch the game summary (`/summary?event={id}`) to discover all participating players -- including those no longer on any roster.
4. **Profile + gamelog pass**: For each newly discovered player, fetch their full profile from the core API (`sports.core.api.espn.com/v2/.../athletes/{id}`) and their gamelog for the target season.

### ESPN Endpoints Used

| Endpoint | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `site.api.espn.com/apis/site/v2/sports/football/nfl/teams` | List all 32 teams |
| `site.api.espn.com/.../teams/{id}/roster` | Current roster (no season param) |
| `site.api.espn.com/apis/common/v3/.../athletes/{id}/gamelog?season=YYYY` | Player gamelog (works for historical seasons) |
| `site.api.espn.com/.../summary?event={id}` | Game boxscore with all participating players |
| `sports.core.api.espn.com/v2/.../athletes/{id}` | Full player profile (name, position, DOB, height, weight, headshot) |

